---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const repo = 'https://github.com/BradEwing/rcb-database';
---

<Layout title="About — Santa Monica Rent-Control Registry">
  <article class="prose">
    <p class="back"><a href={`${base}/`}>← Back to the map</a></p>

    <h1>About this registry</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A self-hosted map of Santa Monica's rent-controlled housing, rebuilt each
      month from the City's public Maximum Allowable Rent (MAR) lookup tool. It's
      the source of truth for tracking how the MAR of every controlled unit
      changes over time.
    </p>

    <h2>What is the MAR?</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>Maximum Allowable Rent</strong> is the legal rent ceiling for a
      rent-controlled unit. It moves with the annual General Adjustment (effective
      around September 1), Board-approved adjustments, and tenancy resets. A
      <strong>$0</strong> MAR means the unit is currently exempt (e.g. Costa-Hawkins
      vacancy decontrol, Ellis-withdrawn, or post-1978 exempt).
    </p>

    <h2>Counts &amp; the RCB caveat</h2>
    <p>
      The MAR tool returns a row for every unit with an established MAR — a
      <em>superset</em> of the Rent Control Board's published "controlled units"
      headline, which excludes rent-level-decontrolled single-family homes and
      condos, owner-occupied 2–3 unit exemptions, and other use-exempt units that
      can still carry a positive MAR. So the registry's positive-MAR total runs
      above the RCB headline by design — it is definitional, not a scraping error.
      We publish both the registry total and an RCB-comparable estimate
      (controlled units on 4+ unit parcels). See the
      <a href={`${repo}/blob/main/docs/reconciliation-2025.md`}>reconciliation memo</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>How the map is built</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Each unit is grouped under its <strong>APN</strong> (LA County parcel number).</li>
      <li>
        Parcel polygons come from the City's
        <strong>Parcels Public</strong> layer, joined to the registry by APN
        (~99% coverage; unmatched parcels are reported in the footer).
      </li>
      <li>
        The observation history is an event-sourced change log — one row per
        change, carried forward — so the colour and the per-parcel change list
        reflect real MAR movements, attributed by whether the tenancy date moved
        (new tenancy) or not (adjustment). No GA formula is reconstructed.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.smgov.net/departments/rentcontrol/mar.aspx">City of Santa Monica — MAR lookup tool</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.smgov.net/Departments/RentControl/content.aspx?id=44652">Rent Control program info &amp; street list</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://gis-smgov.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/smgov::parcels-public-1/explore">City of Santa Monica / LA County — Parcels Public</a></li>
      <li>Basemap © <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>, © <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OpenStreetMap</a> contributors.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cadence &amp; licensing</h2>
    <p>
      The registry refreshes monthly via a scheduled GitHub Action; the map
      rebuilds automatically when the data commits. Code is MIT-licensed; the
      registry data is released CC0. Full source and data:
      <a href={repo}>{repo.replace('https://github.com/', '')}</a>.
    </p>

    <footer id="provenance" class="provenance">Loading build provenance…</footer>
  </article>
</Layout>

<script>
  import { dataUrl } from '../config';
  import type { SiteMeta } from '../lib/types';

  const el = document.getElementById('provenance');
  if (el) {
    fetch(dataUrl('meta.json'))
      .then((r) => (r.ok ? (r.json() as Promise<SiteMeta>) : Promise.reject(r.status)))
      .then((m) => {
        const built = new Date(m.built_at).toISOString().slice(0, 10);
        const sha = (m.source_sha || '').slice(0, 7);
        const pct = (m.match_rate * 100).toFixed(1);
        el.textContent =
          `Latest sweep ${m.latest_sweep} · built ${built} from ${sha} · ` +
          `${m.parcels_mapped.toLocaleString()}/${m.parcels_total.toLocaleString()} parcels mapped ` +
          `(${pct}%, ${m.parcels_unmatched} unmatched) · ${m.units_total.toLocaleString()} units.`;
      })
      .catch(() => {
        el.textContent = '';
      });
  }
</script>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }
  .back {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .back a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .provenance {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--muted) 30%, transparent);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
</style>
